Gibran Bassil apologizes to his mother: & quot;
03 Nov 2019, 13:16 by Lebanon 24
While the head of the Free Patriotic Movement (FPM), minister in the caretaker government, Gebran Bassil was addressing the crowds on Baabda Palace Road, his supporters interrupted him with the song “Hella Hella Hila Ho… Hibran Bassil Menhbou”. After that he went to his mother, and said: "I apologize to you because of me because of your harm and you are not guilty, but you taught me the love of Lebanon, and that my personal dignity is not more important than the dignity of my homeland. Shaw my Lord, you endured a lot but time will tell the truth. "
